BOARDROOM MODEL ASSIGNMENTS — 3 TIERS
  Every board member has 3 inference tiers. All cloud models from Ollama cloud library.
  Tier 1 = local (pulled on VPS). Tier 2 = cloud mid (default). Tier 3 = cloud max (critical/constitutional).
  Importance routing: routine/standard → Tier 2, critical/constitutional → Tier 3.

  Member            Tier 1 (local)          Tier 2 (cloud mid)          Tier 3 (cloud max)
  ─────────────     ──────────────          ──────────────────          ──────────────────
  CEO               qwen3:0.6b              glm-5.1                     glm-5 (744B/40B)
  COO (1.0x)        qwen3:0.6b              gemini-3-flash-preview      ministral-3:14b
  CFO (1.0x)        deepseek-coder:1.3b     qwen3.5:9b                  qwen3.5:122b
  CTO (1.0x)        qwen3:1.7b              qwen3-coder-next            devstral-2 (123B)
  CISO (1.2x veto)  deepseek-r1:1.5b        nemotron-3-super (120B)     qwen3-next (80B)
  CLO (0.8x adv)    qwen3:0.6b              devstral-small-2:24b        cogito-2.1 (671B)
  CPO (1.0x)        qwen3.5:2b              gemma4:31b                  kimi-k2.5
  CRO (1.2x veto)   qwen3:4b               deepseek-v3.2               minimax-m2.7

  Cloud pool (available for general agents):
  nemotron-3-nano (4b,30b), minimax-m2.5, minimax-m2, glm-4.7, rnj-1 (8b)

CAPABILITIES
- name: chat
  description: Multi-turn conversation with cloud models
  rate_limited: true

- name: generate
  description: Single-turn text generation
  rate_limited: true

- name: embed
  description: Text embeddings via cloud models
  rate_limited: true

- name: list_models
  description: Fetch available cloud model catalog (cached, no rate limit)
  rate_limited: false

- name: show_model
  description: Get model details, capabilities, parameters
  rate_limited: false

- name: web_search
  description: Web search via Ollama API (requires OLLAMA_API_KEY)
  rate_limited: false

- name: web_fetch
  description: Fetch and parse web content (requires OLLAMA_API_KEY)
  rate_limited: false

- name: get_metrics
  description: Cloud usage metrics — 18dp precision tracking
  rate_limited: false

- name: get_status
  description: Rate limiter status, quota utilization, session info
  rate_limited: false

INTEGRATION
- VLLMHandler: cloud fallback when local vLLM unreachable (same /v1/ protocol)
- Boardroom: soldiers query cloud models via local proxy (transparent routing)
- BDI Agent: provider cascade includes cloud as last-resort inference
- InferenceDiscovery: ollama_cloud registered as always-AVAILABLE source
- PrecisionMetricsTracker: actual token counts at 18dp (cypherpunk2048 standard)
- Warchest/Shotgun: cloud included in parallel blast

VLLM BRIDGE
  VLLMHandler at localhost:11434 transparently routes to cloud when:
  1. Local vLLM server unreachable
  2. Model name matches a cloud model (deepseek-v3.2, qwen3-coder-next, etc.)
  3. `ollama signin` completed on VPS (local daemon handles auth)
  No separate OLLAMA_API_KEY needed for free tier.

OPERATING PRINCIPLES
  - Cloud is extension, not replacement
  - Rate limits are ammunition — spend wisely
  - Every cloud request logged with actual token counts (no estimation)
  - Adaptive pacing: slow down as utilization rises, don't hit the wall
  - Precision at 18 decimal places — spending .01 to earn .011 is profit
  - Free tier first — pay only when free tier is insufficient

PERSONA
  voice: efficient, precise, resource-aware
  tradition: cypherpunk — trust the math
  identity: I am the gateway between local reasoning and cloud power.

SINGLETON: true
MEMORY_AGENT: optional
COORDINATOR: dispatchable
AUTHORITY_LEVEL: tool

END
